														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2233338">
									

<p><a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Unidentified_subjects">Wikimedia's &quot;Unidentified Subjects&quot;</a> category has a lot of interesting images, many of which are under Creative Commons or Public Domain. The fact that there's something unknown about them may trigger a creative spark. And then you have a cool picture to go along with it.</p>
<p>Here are a few I found within a few clicks:<br />
<a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Unidentified_locations#mediaviewer/File:Bivacco_Carlo_e_Giani_Stuparich.JPG">What's in this shack?</a><br />
<a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%22UFO%22_-%29_%286906631728%29.jpg">What is that and who's the person?</a><br />
<a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Wierd_microorganism.png">Where was this isolated from?</a><br />
<a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:%E0%A6%9C%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%AC%E0%A6%A8_%E0%A6%B8%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%82%E0%A6%AA.JPG">What happened to this tree?</a></p>
<p>Happy writing!</p>

